        public static SolidFireElement create(String mvip,
                                      String username,
                                      String password)
        Create a new instance of SolidFireElement with a connection to the given target with the appropriate username and password. Hostname verification is defaulted to false.
        Parameters:
        mvip - the management virtual IP (MVIP)
        username - admin username
        password - admin password
        Returns:
        an instance of the SolidFire Element

      • create

        public static SolidFireElement create(String target,
                                      String username,
                                      String password,
                                      boolean verifySSL)
        Create a new instance of SolidFireElement with a connection to the given target with the appropriate username and password. The instance will be initialized at the maximum supported version of the API.
        Parameters:
        target - the management virtual IP (or hostname)
        username - admin username
        password - admin password
        verifySSL - if set to true, the target will be checked against the list of valid SSL hosts, including verification of the validity of the Cert recorded for a given target, otherwise these validity checks are ignored, which is useful when the target is an IP address.
        Returns:
        an instance of the SolidFire Element
        See Also:
        getMaxApiVersion()
